CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 2, 1966, pg. 12A, reads: "Happy Spartan Rooters - It was a bunch of happy rooters at the Civic Arena Saturday night as Schenley High School nailed down the state high school basketball championship by defeating Chester.  Shown above are just some of the thousands on hand to root Schenley to victory... Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Crowd in stands for championship basketball game, Schenley High School versus Uniontown, University of Pittsburgh Field House
